cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.DB 

This paper discusses the collection and handling of digital evidence, which is a common topic in the computer security (cs.CR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new digital evidence bag specifically for evidence gathered from P2P networks, which involves network communication and metadata generation, making it relevant to the software engineering (cs.SE), cyber security (cs.CY), and database (cs.DB) sub-categories.
